1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,310
When combining two or more data sets together,

2
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:07,035
pandas provides an incredible tool called concat.

3
00:00:07,035 --> 00:00:13,260
Concat takes a list of one or more DataFrames and joins them vertically or horizontally.

4
00:00:13,260 --> 00:00:15,930
Here you can see them vertically.

5
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:20,475
Think of this as stacking one DataFrame on top of another.

6
00:00:20,475 --> 00:00:23,250
Pandas tries to align all of the columns

7
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:27,675
together by joining and matching on the column names.

8
00:00:27,675 --> 00:00:33,560
The return value of concat is a new DataFrame from the joint results.

9
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:36,665
By default, concat joins vertically.

10
00:00:36,665 --> 00:00:41,330
Or you can explicitly state it by using the axis equal to zero.

11
00:00:41,330 --> 00:00:45,985
To join horizontally, one must set axis equal to one.

12
00:00:45,985 --> 00:00:48,920
Concat includes additional parameters allowing

13
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:51,725
you to combine your DataFrames in different ways.

14
00:00:51,725 --> 00:00:53,585
Let's go through the Jupyter Notebook,

15
00:00:53,585 --> 00:00:56,220
and practice using this amazing tool.

